article.headline: Cornell 63, Dartmouth 47
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Adam Gore made six 3-pointers and finished with 20 points to lead Cornell to a 63-47 win over Dartmouth on Friday night. Gore scored 14 of his points in the first half as the Big Red (8-11, 3-2 Ivy) never trailed. Cornell jumped out to a 13-3 lead and was up 38-23 at the break. Graham Dow added 12 points and Andrew Naeve 10 rebounds. Calvin Arnold came off the bench to score 11 points and grab eight rebounds for Dartmouth (2-16, 0-5). The Big Green pulled to 52-41 with 6:54 to play but couldn't get any closer.
